# Starter Project Configuration for OzusNews

## Plugins
- com.android.application
- org.jetbrains.kotlin.android
- org.jetbrains.kotlin.kapt
- dagger.hilt.android.plugin

## Android Build Settings
- compileSdk: 34
- minSdk: 24
- targetSdk: 34
- buildFeatures: compose = true, buildConfig = true
- composeOptions: kotlinCompilerExtensionVersion = "1.5.4"
- kotlinOptions: jvmTarget = "1.8"

## Dependencies
- Jetpack Compose (ui, material3, tooling, activity-compose, navigation-compose)
- Hilt (hilt-android, hilt-compiler, hilt-navigation-compose)
- Retrofit (retrofit, converter-gson)
- Room (room-runtime, room-ktx, room-compiler, room-paging)
- Paging 3 (paging-runtime, room-paging)
- Coil (coil-compose)
- DataStore (datastore-preferences)
- WorkManager (work-runtime-ktx)
- Lifecycle (lifecycle-runtime-ktx, lifecycle-viewmodel-compose)
- Coroutines (core, android)
- Testing (junit, junit-android, espresso, compose-ui-test, hilt-android-testing)

## Secure API Key Handling
- Store API keys in local.properties (e.g., newsapi.key=YOUR_NEWSAPI_KEY_HERE)
- Expose via BuildConfig in build.gradle.kts

## AndroidX
- gradle.properties: android.useAndroidX=true

## Dependency Repositories
- google()
- mavenCentral()
- gradlePluginPortal()

## Notes
- Use Hilt for dependency injection
- Use Room for local database
- Use Retrofit for network/API
- Use Paging 3 for paginated data
- Use DataStore for preferences
- Use WorkManager for background tasks
- Use Coil for image loading
- Use Jetpack Compose for UI